.SH "Obtaining and verifying"
.PP
The git tag for each release (e\&.g\&. \fRv0\&.6\&.0\fP) is GPG-signed by one of the maintainers\&. For a fully verified build of this project, it is recommended to obtain this repository via git, obtain the GPG keys of the signing maintainer(s), and then verify the release tag's signature using git\&.

.PP
This can be done with the following steps:

.PP
.IP "1." 4
Obtain the GPG keys listed in \fBSECURITY\&.md\fP\&.
.IP "2." 4
If possible, cross-reference these key IDs with another source controlled by its owner (e\&.g\&. social media, personal website)\&. This is to mitigate the unlikely case that incorrect content is being presented by this repository\&.
.IP "3." 4
Clone the repository: 
.PP
.nf
git clone https://github\&.com/bitcoin\-core/secp256k1

.fi
.PP

.IP "4." 4
Check out the latest release tag, e\&.g\&. 
.PP
.nf
git checkout v0\&.6\&.0

.fi
.PP

.IP "5." 4
Use git to verify the GPG signature: 
.PP
