.SH "Benchmark"
.PP
If configured with \fR--enable-benchmark\fP (which is the default), binaries for benchmarking the libsecp256k1 functions will be present in the root directory after the build\&.

.PP
To print the benchmark result to the command line: 
.PP
.nf
$ \&./bench_name

.fi
.PP

.PP
To create a CSV file for the benchmark result : 
.PP
.nf
$ \&./bench_name | sed '2d;s/ \\{1,\\}//g' > bench_name\&.csv

.fi
